                "institute": "2JPNJAE"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The Japan Research Reactor-3 (JRR-3) in JAEA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The HR-2 irradiation hole in JRR-3.",
                "The proportion of epi-thermal neutron flux component to",
                "total neutron flux was less than 1%.",
                "The HR can be considered as a well-thermalized neutron",
                "field."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "An enriched 204Pb metal sample with a mass of 15.13",
                "mg was used for a Pb sample.",
                "Two sets of two Au/Al alloy wires with weights of",
                "0.5 mg and 1.0 mg and a 1.2 mg Mo metal foil was",
                "used as a neutron flux monitor.",
                "One of the monitors was irradiated for 30 minutes.",
                "Subsequently, the Pb sample was irradiated",
                "for 576 hours (24 days).",
                "After the irradiation of the Pb sample, the other",
                "monitor was irradiated for 30 minutes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "ASEP",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The enriched 204Pb sample was",
                "irradiated for a long period with thermal neutrons",
                "in the JRR-3.",
                "After irradiation, the sample was analysed by thermal",
                "ionization mass spectrometry (TIMS) technique.",
                "The thermal neutron capture cross section of 204Pb was",
                "determined from the isotopic ratio between 205Pb and",
                "204Pb and measured neutron flux.",
                "The neutron flux components were derived from the",
                "gamma-ray spectral data of the flux monitors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP",
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The isotopic ratios of Pb sample were",
                "analysed by TIMS. The mass analysis was performed",
                "using the mass spectrometer TRITON-T1 (Thermo",
                "Fisher Scientific,Inc. USA). The decay gamma-rays",
                "from the monitors were measured with a high purity",
                "germanium detector, relative efficiency of 20%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The net isotopic ratio 205Pb/204Pb was derived with",
                "TIMS.",
                "The neutron flux was derived with the Westcott",
                "convention method using the gamma-ray yields,",
                "the thermal cross section of Au, the sensitivity to",
                "epi-thermal neutrons, and the g-factors of the monitor",
                "materials.",
                "These values were taken from the REL-REF.",
                "The thermal cross section of Mo-37 was taken from",
                "an Authors' previous experiment. (Not published yet.)",
                "The deduced Westcott index is enough small and the",
                "epithermal component was negligibly small.",
                "The influences of double neutron capture events and",
                "decay events of 205Pb were also negligible.",
                "The thermal neutron capture cross section of 204Pb was",
                "determined from the isotopic ratio between 205Pb and",
                "204Pb and derived neutron flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
